description.narrative: By end 2021, communities, parents, young people and children have the knowledge and are empowered to access quality education services and engage effectively in inclusive community approaches to education, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Early Childhood Development, Education â€“ General, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Equity â€“ Focus On Girls' And Inclusive Education, Learning Outcomes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 5: By the end of 2021, the most vulnerable preschool and school-age children, adolescents and young people, of both sexes, in the 10 targeted provinces make greater use of inclusive, quality educational services, for improved learning outcomes and receive certification for this.

description.narrative: UNICEF support focused on strengthening Parents' Associations (APE) and their autonomy. Demand for education exists in Chad, but school fees are a significant burden for many families, impacting on the education of children, especially girls. 720 vulnerable APEs benefited from subsidies to support their community teachers, and almost 300 APEs were trained in the management of school management committees and in the use of new technologies for real-time monitoring. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:08/02/2020
